N = int(input())
if N % 2 == 0:
    print(N)
else:
    print(N * 2)


This solution works by taking the input, N, and checking if it is divisible by 2. If it is, the solution simply prints N. If it isn't, the solution multiplies N by 2 and prints the result. This is because the smallest positive integer divisible by both 2 and N is simply N if N is divisible by 2, and N*2 if N is not divisible by 2.
